cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques applied to medical imaging data, specifically chest X-rays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of natural language processing to extract disease labels from radiological reports suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with a large-scale dataset, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
